<br>
One reason you may seem to see a lot of Wizards post 50, as opposed to sub-50, is that by 50+ and certainly by 60, most of us are immensely proud of our levels and also have developed a tough enough skin to not require /anon to avoid port beggars.<br>
<br>
The best way to get groups is build your rep... catch 22 you may think if you rarely get groups, but it is part of the challenge. Your guild should be supportive of you as well. <br>
<br>
After porting 9 groups to Hate as the only Wiz on raid and being the only evaccer at the end of raid, people started to appreciate me a bit more. (only a bit mind you).<br>
<br>
Start to network, learn who the other Wizards on server at your level are. Find out where they are hunting, see if you are missing an opportunity, or have overlooked a possibility.<br>
<br>
Most of all, try and let tonight go. If the xp is irrecoverable, brooding on it will only make you more unhappy.<br>
<br>
